      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems with known analytical solutions confirm correct implementation of element formulations and contact algorithms.",
      "rationale": "Patch tests and cantilever beam benchmarks were used to verify element formulations. Contact algorithm verification performed against Hertzian contact solutions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates QoI change less than 5% between successive refinements.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh convergence study was performed on the pedicle screw shank and screw-rod interface regions. QoI (stiffness, yield force) changed by less than 3% between medium and fine mesh, confirming adequate discretization."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual norms and energy balance checked at each load increment; iterative solver tolerance set to 1e-6.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear solver convergence was monitored via force and displacement residual norms. No convergence failures observed across all 11 construct simulations. Energy balance errors remained below 0.1%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of model setup by a second analyst; documented simulation input files archived.",
      "rationale": "Model setup was independently reviewed by a second FEA analyst at each of the three organizations. Simulation input decks are archived in version-controlled repositories with documented review records."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear elastic constitutive model with bilinear plasticity appropriate for titanium alloy under quasi-static loading; contact formulation captures screw-rod interface behavior.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity was applied to the titanium alloy screw and rod. Frictional contact (mu=0.3) was used at the screw-rod and rod-block interfaces. Model form is consistent with ASTM F1717 quasi-static loading regime."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from coupon testing of same material lot; geometry from CAD nominal dimensions confirmed against CMM measurements.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa), yield strength (880 MPa), and tangent modulus were derived from tensile coupon tests on the same titanium alloy lot used in bench testing. Geometry was taken from nominal CAD and confirmed against CMM data showing deviations less than 0.05 mm."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 constructs from production lot; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to nominal geometry.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were assembled from a single production lot and dimensionally inspected. All constructs fell within drawing tolerances, supporting use of nominal geometry in the FEA model."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Multiple load conditions or loading rates tested to characterize model behavior across the COU envelope.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration. Only one load condition was evaluated, which is below the required level for this factor. This gap is acknowledged and accepted given corroborating evidence from the multi-laboratory design."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions and loading replicate ASTM F1717 test fixture constraints within documented tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Displacement-controlled loading applied at the crosshead attachment point; fixed boundary conditions at the block simulating ASTM F1717 fixture. Equivalency confirmed by comparing reaction force profiles between simulation and test."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All QoI differences less than 10% and E/uval less than 1.96 for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement.",
      "rationale": "Across all three QoIs, the maximum QoI difference was 7.2% (yield force, FDA model). E/uval values ranged from 0.41 to 1.73, all below the 1.96 threshold. Acceptance criteria met for all three FEA platforms."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) directly correspond to clinical performance metrics for pedicle screw fatigue and fracture risk assessment.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the spine; yield force and force at 40 mm displacement are surrogate endpoints for fracture risk under physiological loading. These QoIs are directly linked to the regulatory submission performance criteria."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
